            <title><![CDATA[Star Fox Looks Fucked Up]]></title>
            <link>https://aftermath.site/star-fox-64-remake-nintendo-direct/</link>
            <guid>1512559</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div id="main">
      
    <div data-post-hero="fullwidth-image">

    <div data-post-hero-content="">
          

      

        <p>They massacred my boy (complimentary?)</p>

        
    </div>

      <figure>
          <picture>
  <source srcset="https://storage.ghost.io/c/30/f5/30f5b1bb-84ee-4c26-b446-fb9a5e512994/content/images/size/w320/format/webp/2026/05/fawkes.png 320w, https://storage.ghost.io/c/30/f5/30f5b1bb-84ee-4c26-b446-fb9a5e512994/content/images/size/w640/format/webp/2026/05/fawkes.png 600w, https://storage.ghost.io/c/30/f5/30f5b1bb-84ee-4c26-b446-fb9a5e512994/content/images/size/w960/format/webp/2026/05/fawkes.png 960w, https://storage.ghost.io/c/30/f5/30f5b1bb-84ee-4c26-b446-fb9a5e512994/content/images/size/w1280/format/webp/2026/05/fawkes.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1023px) 90vw, 1200px" type="image/webp">
  
</picture>
        <figcaption><span>Nintendo</span></figcaption>
      </figure>

  </div>

<div data-post-date-group="" data-post-info="">
      <p><span>Published:</span>
        <time datetime="2026-05-06T07:06:57">May 06, 2026, 7:06 pm</time>
      </p>
    </div>
    <article>
      <p>Today Nintendo went live with <a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/ePZeyh5q9R8?ref=aftermath.site"><u>a surprise Direct</u></a> to debut a Switch 2 remake of <em>Star Fox 64</em>. It is the first new (or new-ish) <em>Star Fox</em> game since 2016. Cool! Great! We love to see it! Or we would if not for the fact that Fox and his furry flotilla of friends look…wrong.&nbsp;</p><figure><iframe width="200" height="113" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ePZeyh5q9R8?start=1215&amp;feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen="" title="Star Fox Direct 5.6.2026"></iframe></figure><p>Long have the people clamored for a Nintendo game with hyperrealistic graphics. Finally, they got one, and it’s the series that stars cartoon animals. The monkey’s paw, also as realistic as modern hardware can render, curls. Before the Direct was even over, unflattering comparisons started rolling in:</p>
<!--kg-card-begin: html-->
<blockquote data-bluesky-uri="at://did:plc:jcy5tnrrvxg4yrh2qxsgzu5p/app.bsky.feed.post/3ml7ph5lu3c2u" data-bluesky-cid="bafyreiaxekj362oiokarujwu75basv5egysgn27fzhocpkglvoh4gzayke" data-bluesky-embed-color-mode="system">— Jacob Geller (<a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:jcy5tnrrvxg4yrh2qxsgzu5p?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">@jacobgeller.com</a>) <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:jcy5tnrrvxg4yrh2qxsgzu5p/post/3ml7ph5lu3c2u?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">May 6, 2026 at 3:04 PM</a></blockquote>
<!--kg-card-end: html-->

<!--kg-card-begin: html-->
<blockquote data-bluesky-uri="at://did:plc:v7grokiek2j2fehsd53efi64/app.bsky.feed.post/3ml7qcjgsf22s" data-bluesky-cid="bafyreidm5uaen32aqccn3ntsqx5b7bx5qzciqsdasjhxm5qurs2vqc4dbm" data-bluesky-embed-color-mode="system">— Topher Florence (<a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:v7grokiek2j2fehsd53efi64?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">@topherflorence.bsky.social</a>) <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:v7grokiek2j2fehsd53efi64/post/3ml7qcjgsf22s?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">May 6, 2026 at 3:20 PM</a></blockquote>
<!--kg-card-end: html-->

<!--kg-card-begin: html-->
<blockquote data-bluesky-uri="at://did:plc:4hnfwhumysj73juuhqjxrgo2/app.bsky.feed.post/3ml7qxvbkgk2u" data-bluesky-cid="bafyreiftc66o4tlnp2bjnhqb7k4a4jqtwxxa4zp3tj7hftpaiovxgllk54" data-bluesky-embed-color-mode="system">— Bud Starved Beast (<a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:4hnfwhumysj73juuhqjxrgo2?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">@budstarved.bsky.social</a>) <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:4hnfwhumysj73juuhqjxrgo2/post/3ml7qxvbkgk2u?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">May 6, 2026 at 3:32 PM</a></blockquote>
<!--kg-card-end: html-->
<p>To hear some tell it, <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/woahitsjuanito.bsky.social/post/3ml7qdm7krs2d?ref=aftermath.site"><u>even the furries are upset</u></a>.</p><p>But <em>Star Fox</em> has always been an odd proposition; maybe Nintendo’s just decided to embrace that strangeness to the fullest extent possible, rather than unknowingly bungling its way into a Sonic-with-human-teeth situation. If nothing else, it’s clearly having fun puppeteering its weird new ani-mannequins, so much so that it’s decided we should be able to as well. During the Direct, Nintendo also showed off a new feature that will let you change your face in game chat to look like a <em>Star Fox</em> character. This is no static image, either; when you move, Fox moves. Basically, you get your own<em> Star Fox</em> Vtuber. Opinions on this have varied, but I think it absolutely rules.</p>
<!--kg-card-begin: html-->
<blockquote data-bluesky-uri="at://did:plc:vw4sfkfvggi2a3mbfm2xgh52/app.bsky.feed.post/3ml7q2z65bk2w" data-bluesky-cid="bafyreigamnlicoeddrbecs2dwkwl2vmku43j7e4nhk44qjq7ygy5pcv3ge" data-bluesky-embed-color-mode="system">— lex luddy (ichiban appreciator) (<a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:vw4sfkfvggi2a3mbfm2xgh52?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">@lexluddy.xyz</a>) <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:vw4sfkfvggi2a3mbfm2xgh52/post/3ml7q2z65bk2w?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">May 6, 2026 at 3:15 PM</a></blockquote>
<!--kg-card-end: html-->

<!--kg-card-begin: html-->
<blockquote data-bluesky-uri="at://did:plc:idpr7cxv2u34lmpvap62t7kp/app.bsky.feed.post/3ml7q4eulbk2c" data-bluesky-cid="bafyreigx646mmwq5pcwktsdbnctuzq3uo74dg24lyjrrexnjmgb44mrzhy" data-bluesky-embed-color-mode="system">— AmericanTruckSongs10 (<a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:idpr7cxv2u34lmpvap62t7kp?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">@ethangach.bsky.social</a>) <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:idpr7cxv2u34lmpvap62t7kp/post/3ml7q4eulbk2c?ref_src=embed&amp;ref=aftermath.site">May 6, 2026 at 3:16 PM</a></blockquote>
<!--kg-card-end: html-->
<p>So yeah, Fox and company looked fucked up now. This is an objective fact. But can we put a qualitative judgement on that? No. It could as easily be a grave portent as it could be a sign of good things to come. Fortunately, we won’t have to wait long. <em>Star Fox </em>releases on June 25. </p><h2 id="recommended">Recommended</h2><figure><a href="https://aftermath.site/if-link-talks-i-walk/"><div><p>If Link Talks, I Walk - Aftermath</p><p>The only acceptable forms of communication for Link are hiiiiyah, break jar, and journalism</p><p><span>Nathan Grayson</span></p></div></a></figure>
    </article>

